│ Based on the root cause analysis, the issue stems from the   │
│ vectorizer incorrectly assuming a value is uniform across    │
│ vector lanes when its calculation is predicated. This        │
│ happens because the logic to detect when a value needs to be │
│ widened (i.e., turned into a vector) is too restrictive.     │
│                                                              │
│ The analysis points to a condition that incorrectly limits   │
│ this check. The problematic logic is in                      │
│ `VPlanConstruction.cpp`, where `VPInstruction`s are created. │
│ The check `DefI->getParent() != BB` is too narrow. It fails  │
│ to account for cases where an instruction uses an operand    │
│ that, while defined in the same basic block, depends on a    │
│ predicated value from another lane.                          │
│                                                              │
│ The correct approach is to mark an instruction for widening  │
│ if any of its operands are defined within the loop,          │
│ regardless of whether it's in the same basic block or not.   │
│ This ensures that if an operand's value can vary between     │
│ vector lanes due to control flow, the instruction using it   │
│ will be properly vectorized.                                 │
│                                                              │
│ The fix is to remove the `DefI->getParent() != BB` part of   │
│ the condition, leaving only                                  │
│ `TheLoop->contains(DefI->getParent())`. This correctly       │
│ identifies that if an operand is defined anywhere inside the │
│ loop, the result might not be uniform and thus must be       │
│ widened.                                                     │
│                                                              │
│ ```diff                                                      │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanConstruction.cpp    │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanConstruction.cpp    │
│ @@ -233,7 +233,7 @@                                          │
│        for (VPValue *V : VPOperands) {                       │
│          if (auto *DefR =                                    │
│ dyn_cast_or_null<VPRecipeBase>(V->getDef())) {               │
│            if (auto *DefI = DefR->getUnderlyingInstr()) {    │
│ -            if (DefI->getParent() != BB &&                  │
│ TheLoop->contains(DefI->getParent())) {                      │
│ +            if (TheLoop->contains(DefI->getParent())) {     │
│                NewR->setMustBeWidened();                     │
│                break;                                        │
│              }                                               │
│                                                              │
│ ```                                                          │
